US1 Manage stockrooms assigned to a comptoir

As a

Comptoir Manager

I want to

view, add and remove stockrooms assigned to my comptoir, and define a display name for each

So that

technicians can use clear and simplified names while keeping the original stockroom reference

⸻

Description

A new section “Stockrooms management” is available in the comptoir settings, following the same UX pattern as Access rights management.

This section allows the manager to:
	•	view all stockrooms assigned to the comptoir
	•	add a stockroom via a search flow
	•	define a display name at the time of addition
	•	display both:
	•	the display name (primary label)
	•	the real stockroom name (secondary label)
	•	remove a stockroom

The display name is a user-friendly label defined at comptoir level, while the real name remains the technical reference.

⸻

UX Behavior

Main view (similar to Access rights management)
	•	Card titled: Stockrooms management
	•	List of assigned stockrooms
	•	Each row displays:
	•	Display name (main text)
	•	Real stockroom name (secondary text)
	•	Remove (X) action on the right

⸻

Add stockroom flow (modal)

Same pattern as “Add a viewer”:

Step 1 – Search
	•	Input field:
Enter stockroom name or ID

Step 2 – Select
	•	Display matching stockrooms
	•	User selects one

Step 3 – Display name
	•	Mandatory input:
Enter display name
	•	Pre-filled with real name (recommended)

Actions
	•	Validate
	•	Cancel

⸻

Business Rules
	•	A stockroom can only be assigned once per comptoir
	•	The display name is mandatory
	•	The real stockroom name is read-only and cannot be modified
	•	The display name is defined at creation time
	•	Only authorized managers can add or remove stockrooms
	•	Removing a stockroom makes it immediately unavailable for technicians

⸻

Acceptance Criteria

AC1 View stockrooms

Given I am a manager
When I open the stockrooms section
Then I see the list of assigned stockrooms
And each row displays:
	•	display name
	•	real stockroom name

⸻

AC2 Empty state

Given no stockroom is assigned
Then an empty state is displayed
And an Add button is available

⸻

AC3 Open add flow

Given I click on Add stockroom
Then a modal opens
And I can search for a stockroom

⸻

AC4 Search stockroom

When I type in the search field
Then matching stockrooms are displayed

⸻

AC5 Select stockroom

When I select a stockroom
Then I can proceed to define a display name

⸻

AC6 Display name required

When I validate the creation
Then the display name is mandatory
And an error is shown if empty

⸻

AC7 Add stockroom

Given I selected a stockroom and defined a display name
When I validate
Then the stockroom is added
And appears immediately in the list

⸻

AC8 Prevent duplicate

Given the stockroom is already assigned
When I try to add it again
Then the action is blocked
And a clear message is displayed

⸻

AC9 Remove stockroom

When I click on the remove icon
Then the stockroom is removed
And disappears immediately from the list

⸻

AC10 Persistence

When I reload the page
Then the assigned stockrooms remain
And their display names are preserved

⸻

AC11 Authorization

Given I am not authorized
Then I cannot add or remove stockrooms

